00:00:56.870 --> 00:00:59.880 align:middle line:90%
about health and eating.

00:00:59.880 --> 00:01:00.680 align:middle line:90%
Andrew--

00:01:00.680 --> 00:01:01.080 align:middle line:90%
>> Hi.

00:01:01.080 --> 00:01:01.997 align:middle line:90%
>> --welcome back to--

00:01:01.997 --> 00:01:02.910 align:middle line:90%
>> Thank you.

00:01:02.910 --> 00:01:04.590 align:middle line:90%
>> --Wisdom Television.

00:01:04.590 --> 00:01:06.515 align:middle line:84%
It's always a pleasure
to have you here.

00:01:06.515 --> 00:01:08.250 align:middle line:84%
You know, one of
the things that I

00:01:08.250 --> 00:01:10.560 align:middle line:84%
think is so important
about your book

00:01:10.560 --> 00:01:15.520 align:middle line:84%
is that we have forgotten
about food being a pleasure.

00:01:15.520 --> 00:01:18.780 align:middle line:10%
>> I think a real problem in
this culture is that people

00:01:18.780 --> 00:01:21.300 align:middle line:10%
make an opposition between
healthy food and delicious

00:01:21.300 --> 00:01:23.910 align:middle line:10%
food, and think that, if
you want to be healthy,

00:01:23.910 --> 00:01:26.310 align:middle line:10%
you have to give up
everything you know like.

00:01:26.310 --> 00:01:29.080 align:middle line:84%
One of my purposes is to show
people that that's not true,

00:01:29.080 --> 00:01:32.730 align:middle line:84%
that it's perfectly possible
to design a diet and eating

00:01:32.730 --> 00:01:35.550 align:middle line:84%
plan that provides all the
pleasure you want from food

00:01:35.550 --> 00:01:39.640 align:middle line:84%
and also conforms to ideas of
good health and good nutrition.

00:01:39.640 --> 00:01:43.650 align:middle line:84%
>> Another point you make is
that eating is very important,

00:01:43.650 --> 00:01:46.410 align:middle line:84%
never mind just to
nourish our bodies,

00:01:46.410 --> 00:01:48.240 align:middle line:90%
but as a social pastime.

00:01:48.240 --> 00:01:51.840 align:middle line:84%
>> The word companion comes
from the Latin root for bread.

00:01:51.840 --> 00:01:53.820 align:middle line:84%
A companion is somebody
you share bread with.

00:01:53.820 --> 00:01:56.430 align:middle line:84%
I think this is a
fundamental human bond.

00:01:56.430 --> 00:01:58.110 align:middle line:84%
I think the way
you eat also helps

00:01:58.110 --> 00:02:02.310 align:middle line:84%
define your individual
and cultural identity.

00:02:02.310 --> 00:02:07.980 align:middle line:84%
You know, Muslims don't eat
pork, Hindus don't eat meat,

00:02:07.980 --> 00:02:10.110 align:middle line:84%
we eat certain foods
on certain days.

00:02:10.110 --> 00:02:11.760 align:middle line:90%
This is part of your identity.

00:02:11.760 --> 00:02:15.540 align:middle line:84%
I think if you go off on a
way of eating because somebody

00:02:15.540 --> 00:02:17.910 align:middle line:84%
tells you so or you read
something in a book that

00:02:17.910 --> 00:02:20.970 align:middle line:84%
separates you from other
people or from your culture,

00:02:20.970 --> 00:02:25.400 align:middle line:84%
it sabotages that important
purpose of eating.

00:02:25.400 --> 00:02:28.190 align:middle line:84%
>> Do you think it's healthier
to eat with someone than alone?

00:02:28.190 --> 00:02:30.770 align:middle line:90%


00:02:30.770 --> 00:02:37.220 align:middle line:84%
>> I think both are fine, but
I think that the act of eating

00:02:37.220 --> 00:02:40.130 align:middle line:84%
with somebody is one of the most
pleasurable activities that we

00:02:40.130 --> 00:02:40.930 align:middle line:90%
have.

00:02:40.930 --> 00:02:43.850 align:middle line:84%
You know, to share time around
the consumption of food,

00:02:43.850 --> 00:02:45.500 align:middle line:84%
or preparation and
consumption of food,

00:02:45.500 --> 00:02:47.865 align:middle line:84%
I think this is time
very well spent.

00:02:47.865 --> 00:02:50.240 align:middle line:84%
>> One of the things that's
interesting about your book--

00:02:50.240 --> 00:02:52.910 align:middle line:84%
I mean, you're a very
important doctor--

00:02:52.910 --> 00:02:56.720 align:middle line:84%
is that you have your own
personal recipes here.

00:02:56.720 --> 00:02:58.000 align:middle line:90%
>> I like to cook.

00:02:58.000 --> 00:03:00.250 align:middle line:84%
I really learned to cook
when I was in medical school.

00:03:00.250 --> 00:03:03.500 align:middle line:84%
I found that when I
came home from working

00:03:03.500 --> 00:03:05.180 align:middle line:84%
long shifts in
hospitals, I would

00:03:05.180 --> 00:03:07.970 align:middle line:84%
be in such terrible
states of mind.

00:03:07.970 --> 00:03:10.100 align:middle line:84%
I discovered that
cooking, making food

00:03:10.100 --> 00:03:12.050 align:middle line:84%
put me back in a
good mental state.

00:03:12.050 --> 00:03:16.420 align:middle line:84%
It made order, it cleared my
mind, it focused my attention.

00:03:16.420 --> 00:03:18.170 align:middle line:84%
And cooking has always
served me that way.

00:03:18.170 --> 00:03:19.723 align:middle line:84%
It's a kind of
meditation that I do.

00:03:19.723 --> 00:03:20.640 align:middle line:90%
It makes me feel good.

00:03:20.640 --> 00:03:22.640 align:middle line:84%
I like making good
food for other people.

00:03:22.640 --> 00:03:23.840 align:middle line:90%
I invent recipes.

00:03:23.840 --> 00:03:25.340 align:middle line:90%
I test recipes.

00:03:25.340 --> 00:03:28.490 align:middle line:84%
I get very frustrated with
recipes that don't work.

00:03:28.490 --> 00:03:33.320 align:middle line:84%
And I really don't use
cookbooks except to get ideas,

00:03:33.320 --> 00:03:34.907 align:middle line:90%
but then I do things on my own.

00:03:34.907 --> 00:03:36.740 align:middle line:84%
I love being able to
go to a strange kitchen

00:03:36.740 --> 00:03:39.650 align:middle line:84%
and working with whatever's
there to turn out a good meal.

00:03:39.650 --> 00:03:43.610 align:middle line:84%
But I've come to really
like recipes that are quick,

00:03:43.610 --> 00:03:45.860 align:middle line:84%
easy, that don't use a lot
of strange ingredients,

00:03:45.860 --> 00:03:47.360 align:middle line:84%
and that give
really good results,

00:03:47.360 --> 00:03:50.630 align:middle line:84%
both in terms of being tasty
and in terms of being healthy.

00:03:50.630 --> 00:03:53.000 align:middle line:90%
>> What's your favorite spice?

00:03:53.000 --> 00:03:54.350 align:middle line:90%
>> That's a hard one.

00:03:54.350 --> 00:03:55.370 align:middle line:90%
Well, I love red pepper.

00:03:55.370 --> 00:03:56.578 align:middle line:90%
I mean, I like chili peppers.

00:03:56.578 --> 00:04:00.930 align:middle line:84%
I love garlic, which I think
is incredibly healthful.

00:04:00.930 --> 00:04:02.580 align:middle line:84%
One of my favorite
spices is allspice.

00:04:02.580 --> 00:04:03.380 align:middle line:90%
>> Really.

00:04:03.380 --> 00:04:04.340 align:middle line:90%
>> That's a terrific one.

00:04:04.340 --> 00:04:05.140 align:middle line:90%
Yeah, it's great.

00:04:05.140 --> 00:04:10.490 align:middle line:84%
It's great in beans and lentil
soup, anything with squash.

00:04:10.490 --> 00:04:13.340 align:middle line:90%
It gives a wonderful rich taste.

00:04:13.340 --> 00:04:15.890 align:middle line:84%
>> You know, there are a lot
of people who are watching this

00:04:15.890 --> 00:04:18.649 align:middle line:90%
show who live alone.

00:04:18.649 --> 00:04:20.540 align:middle line:84%
And they find
themselves coming home,

00:04:20.540 --> 00:04:23.390 align:middle line:84%
and they get a Weight
Watchers dinner or something,

00:04:23.390 --> 00:04:25.970 align:middle line:84%
or they have
cornflakes and milk.

00:04:25.970 --> 00:04:27.500 align:middle line:90%
>> I'm aware.

00:04:27.500 --> 00:04:29.000 align:middle line:90%
Here's a couple suggestions.

00:04:29.000 --> 00:04:31.550 align:middle line:84%
One is I would like people
to try some of these recipes,

00:04:31.550 --> 00:04:33.350 align:middle line:84%
because they really
are quick and easy.

00:04:33.350 --> 00:04:36.020 align:middle line:84%
And I think that just to see
that food preparation doesn't

00:04:36.020 --> 00:04:37.280 align:middle line:90%
have to be an ordeal.

00:04:37.280 --> 00:04:41.480 align:middle line:84%
But failing that, there are more
and more healthy convenience

00:04:41.480 --> 00:04:42.440 align:middle line:90%
foods available.

00:04:42.440 --> 00:04:45.580 align:middle line:84%
If you go to one of
these good natural foods

00:04:45.580 --> 00:04:47.810 align:middle line:84%
supermarkets that are opening
up around the country,

00:04:47.810 --> 00:04:51.470 align:middle line:84%
and just look through the frozen
food sections or the meals

00:04:51.470 --> 00:04:54.212 align:middle line:84%
in a cup that you just
add boiling water to,

00:04:54.212 --> 00:04:55.670 align:middle line:84%
these are some good
products there.

00:04:55.670 --> 00:04:57.320 align:middle line:84%
You need to read
labels to make sure

00:04:57.320 --> 00:04:59.000 align:middle line:84%
that there are
healthy ingredients,

00:04:59.000 --> 00:05:01.880 align:middle line:84%
but more and more, there are
these healthy convenience

00:05:01.880 --> 00:05:04.250 align:middle line:84%
foods that may work for
people in that situation.

00:05:04.250 --> 00:05:08.450 align:middle line:84%
>> You said in the book
that the shorter the amount

00:05:08.450 --> 00:05:11.940 align:middle line:84%
of ingredients that
are on the label--

00:05:11.940 --> 00:05:12.740 align:middle line:90%
>> The better.

00:05:12.740 --> 00:05:13.540 align:middle line:90%
>> --the better.

00:05:13.540 --> 00:05:14.340 align:middle line:90%
>> Right.

00:05:14.340 --> 00:05:16.490 align:middle line:84%
And also, a good strategy
is think about, you know,

00:05:16.490 --> 00:05:21.448 align:middle line:84%
like let's say you get an
instant cup of corn chowder.

00:05:21.448 --> 00:05:23.240 align:middle line:84%
You know, you just add
boiling water to it.

00:05:23.240 --> 00:05:25.240 align:middle line:84%
Well, think about if you
made corn chowder, what

00:05:25.240 --> 00:05:26.570 align:middle line:90%
would go into it at home.

00:05:26.570 --> 00:05:29.010 align:middle line:84%
Would it be maybe
corn and onions

00:05:29.010 --> 00:05:34.310 align:middle line:84%
and maybe some red pepper,
maybe milk, maybe some olive oil

00:05:34.310 --> 00:05:35.910 align:middle line:90%
or butter.

00:05:35.910 --> 00:05:36.770 align:middle line:90%
That's about it.

00:05:36.770 --> 00:05:39.383 align:middle line:84%
If there's a paragraph
of ingredients there,

00:05:39.383 --> 00:05:41.300 align:middle line:84%
that's probably not
something you want to buy.

00:05:41.300 --> 00:05:44.002 align:middle line:84%
I mean, just see how closely
these products resemble

00:05:44.002 --> 00:05:46.460 align:middle line:84%
what you would do if you were
actually making that at home.

00:05:46.460 --> 00:05:49.230 align:middle line:84%
>> Of course, then the other
thing they do is they say,

00:05:49.230 --> 00:05:51.920 align:middle line:84%
well, first I'll sit down, I'll
have a little glass of wine,

00:05:51.920 --> 00:05:52.942 align:middle line:90%
which you say is fine.

00:05:52.942 --> 00:05:54.525 align:middle line:84%
>> I think that's
fine in moderation--

00:05:54.525 --> 00:05:54.850 align:middle line:90%
>> That's wonderful--

00:05:54.850 --> 00:05:54.940 align:middle line:90%
>> --yeah.

00:05:54.940 --> 00:05:56.450 align:middle line:84%
>> --to have a
drink before dinner.

00:05:56.450 --> 00:06:03.650 align:middle line:84%
And for a snack, I'll have a
bag of this new product that

00:06:03.650 --> 00:06:06.463 align:middle line:90%
says it has no fat at all.

00:06:06.463 --> 00:06:07.880 align:middle line:84%
Olestra, is that
what it's called?

00:06:07.880 --> 00:06:08.420 align:middle line:90%
>> Right.

00:06:08.420 --> 00:06:08.600 align:middle line:90%
Right.

00:06:08.600 --> 00:06:09.400 align:middle line:90%


00:06:09.400 --> 00:06:11.960 align:middle line:84%
>> --potato chips, because
potatoes are good for me.

00:06:11.960 --> 00:06:13.430 align:middle line:90%
I'll get vitamin C.

00:06:13.430 --> 00:06:19.070 align:middle line:84%
>> Probably this new fake
fat that's not absorbed,

00:06:19.070 --> 00:06:21.560 align:middle line:84%
I think the only thing it's
going to do is to increase

00:06:21.560 --> 00:06:25.070 align:middle line:84%
consumption of very low-quality
foods that are not very

00:06:25.070 --> 00:06:27.620 align:middle line:84%
nutritious, that will promote
weight gain in many people.

00:06:27.620 --> 00:06:30.120 align:middle line:84%
I don't think that this is going
to help anyone lose weight.

00:06:30.120 --> 00:06:31.910 align:middle line:84%
It's just going to
encourage people

00:06:31.910 --> 00:06:35.990 align:middle line:84%
to consume more and snack more
on low-quality carbohydrate

00:06:35.990 --> 00:06:38.240 align:middle line:84%
foods that are just the
worst thing you want to eat

00:06:38.240 --> 00:06:39.920 align:middle line:90%
if you're prone to weight gain.

00:06:39.920 --> 00:06:41.180 align:middle line:90%
>> But what about the Olestra?

00:06:41.180 --> 00:06:43.197 align:middle line:84%
Is that a bad
product in general?

00:06:43.197 --> 00:06:44.780 align:middle line:84%
>> I don't think,
in itself, it's bad.

00:06:44.780 --> 00:06:46.790 align:middle line:84%
I mean, it's going to
cause intestinal upsets

00:06:46.790 --> 00:06:48.890 align:middle line:84%
in some people, and
it blocks absorption

00:06:48.890 --> 00:06:50.147 align:middle line:90%
of fat-soluble vitamins.

00:06:50.147 --> 00:06:51.980 align:middle line:84%
I think the main problem
with it, as I said,

00:06:51.980 --> 00:06:54.050 align:middle line:84%
it's going to
increase consumption

00:06:54.050 --> 00:06:55.550 align:middle line:90%
of low-quality foods.

00:06:55.550 --> 00:06:58.160 align:middle line:84%
That will probably
worsen people's situation

00:06:58.160 --> 00:06:59.250 align:middle line:90%
in terms of weight.

00:06:59.250 --> 00:07:01.618 align:middle line:84%
>> On your never-never
list is margarine.

00:07:01.618 --> 00:07:03.410 align:middle line:84%
You don't put Olestra
in the same category.

00:07:03.410 --> 00:07:03.810 align:middle line:90%
>> No, I don't.

00:07:03.810 --> 00:07:06.200 align:middle line:84%
I think margarine is worse
because the fats have

00:07:06.200 --> 00:07:08.480 align:middle line:84%
been chemically altered
in ways that are probably

00:07:08.480 --> 00:07:09.680 align:middle line:90%
very unhealthy for us.

00:07:09.680 --> 00:07:12.222 align:middle line:84%
I think if it comes to a choice
between butter and margarine,

00:07:12.222 --> 00:07:13.223 align:middle line:90%
you take butter.

00:07:13.223 --> 00:07:15.140 align:middle line:84%
I would prefer that
people don't use anything,

00:07:15.140 --> 00:07:18.230 align:middle line:84%
or they use olive oil,
but definitely won't

00:07:18.230 --> 00:07:21.470 align:middle line:84%
eat margarine or all of these
related partially hydrogenated

00:07:21.470 --> 00:07:22.910 align:middle line:84%
oils, which are
now in everything.

00:07:22.910 --> 00:07:26.440 align:middle line:84%
You know, in all commercial
baked goods-- crackers,

00:07:26.440 --> 00:07:27.240 align:middle line:90%
cookies--

00:07:27.240 --> 00:07:29.172 align:middle line:84%
it's all partially
hydrogenated fat.

00:07:29.172 --> 00:07:31.130 align:middle line:84%
>> What does that mean,
partially hydrogenated?

00:07:31.130 --> 00:07:33.020 align:middle line:10%
>> It means that the
fat has been heated,

00:07:33.020 --> 00:07:35.870 align:middle line:10%
liquid oils have been heated
to very high temperatures

00:07:35.870 --> 00:07:39.890 align:middle line:10%
and reacted with hydrogen gas in
the presence of metal catalysts

00:07:39.890 --> 00:07:44.210 align:middle line:10%
in order to convert the oils
to semi-solid forms that have

00:07:44.210 --> 00:07:47.780 align:middle line:10%
longer shelf life and better
baking characteristics.

00:07:47.780 --> 00:07:49.460 align:middle line:90%
Manufacturers love this.

00:07:49.460 --> 00:07:50.930 align:middle line:84%
But in the process
of doing this,

00:07:50.930 --> 00:07:53.570 align:middle line:84%
the molecules that make
up oils are damaged.

00:07:53.570 --> 00:07:55.700 align:middle line:84%
They're changed
from natural forms

00:07:55.700 --> 00:07:58.940 align:middle line:84%
into new forms that are
damaging to our hearts

00:07:58.940 --> 00:08:01.430 align:middle line:84%
and arteries, that promote
cancer and probably

00:08:01.430 --> 00:08:02.970 align:middle line:90%
throat inflammation.

00:08:02.970 --> 00:08:05.930 align:middle line:84%
So this is unhealthy
stuff to put in the body.

00:08:05.930 --> 00:08:09.860 align:middle line:84%
>> What about people who,
no matter what they eat,

00:08:09.860 --> 00:08:13.140 align:middle line:84%
they still have a high
cholesterol count?

00:08:13.140 --> 00:08:15.470 align:middle line:84%
>> In some people, this
is determined genetically,

00:08:15.470 --> 00:08:18.260 align:middle line:84%
and it's relatively
independent of diet.

00:08:18.260 --> 00:08:20.835 align:middle line:84%
There are still some natural
strategies you can try.

00:08:20.835 --> 00:08:23.210 align:middle line:84%
You can try eating garlic,
which helps lower cholesterol.

00:08:23.210 --> 00:08:24.990 align:middle line:90%
You can try eating hot peppers.

00:08:24.990 --> 00:08:28.550 align:middle line:84%
You can try eating shiitake
mushrooms, green tea.

00:08:28.550 --> 00:08:32.059 align:middle line:84%
If that doesn't work, you
could try niacin, a B vitamin,

00:08:32.059 --> 00:08:34.610 align:middle line:84%
which probably should be used
under medical supervision.

00:08:34.610 --> 00:08:36.169 align:middle line:84%
There's a product
called Cholestin,

00:08:36.169 --> 00:08:38.059 align:middle line:84%
which is a red
yeast extract that's

00:08:38.059 --> 00:08:41.120 align:middle line:84%
available widely without
prescription that works.

00:08:41.120 --> 00:08:42.919 align:middle line:84%
And if all else
fails, you can go

00:08:42.919 --> 00:08:44.680 align:middle line:84%
in one of the
cholesterol-lowering drugs.

00:08:44.680 --> 00:08:46.220 align:middle line:90%
>> Are they dangerous?

00:08:46.220 --> 00:08:48.530 align:middle line:84%
>> They may disturb
liver function.

00:08:48.530 --> 00:08:50.630 align:middle line:90%
I don't think they're benign.

00:08:50.630 --> 00:08:53.450 align:middle line:84%
Also, I think lowering
cholesterol is not

00:08:53.450 --> 00:08:55.220 align:middle line:84%
necessarily the
only thing you need

00:08:55.220 --> 00:08:56.910 align:middle line:90%
to do to avoid heart trouble.

00:08:56.910 --> 00:08:59.780 align:middle line:84%
Now, we've put all our attention
on cholesterol, but just

00:08:59.780 --> 00:09:02.300 align:middle line:84%
as an example, there's more
and more people in medicine who

00:09:02.300 --> 00:09:05.390 align:middle line:84%
think that the underlying
problem in coronary heart

00:09:05.390 --> 00:09:08.780 align:middle line:84%
disease is not so much
cholesterol as inflammation,

00:09:08.780 --> 00:09:11.810 align:middle line:84%
that this is an inflammatory
disorder of arteries.

